node.text:
How to make a smooth, soft, pillowy meringue you can use on cake, pie or anything else you desire. It is cooked on the stove, so it is safe to eat without baking. But, feel free to use a blowtorch to toast it! 🔥♥️🤣 

Swiss Meringue Recipe from Zoë Bakes Cakes: www.zoebakes.com (search “Mile High Lime Meringue Tart”) 
Video edited by Henri: @culinaryunprofessional 
Music by my brother: @bluemusic82

Edited 4/17 - I just tried the recipe using a hand held mixer and after 10 minutes it still hasn’t become stiff enough to cover a cake. I will continue to experiment, but at the moment I suggest using a stand mixer if you have one.

node.title: Swiss Meringue from Zoë Bakes Cakes

node.text:
At a super young age I discovered baking brings me joy and feeds my soul. What I've learned from a career in professional kitchens is that I love teaching other people how to bake even more! Now I get to do both, on TV. @joannagaines and @chipgaines have given me a series on their new @magnolianetwork where I can bake, teach and be inspired by some phenomenally talented bakers (and chefs, farmers, bee keepers and more...) in my Minnesota community. 

This is a dream come true and on FRIDAY 2/5 you can watch the first full episode “Porch Party Pies” streaming on @discoveryplus. I’ll be making a lattice pie with strawberries and rhubarb (quintessentially MN and lovingly planted by my dad), plus a simple fruit “Fool” inspired by a trip to visit one of my favorite local pastry chefs, @pastrydiane. You’ll get a glimpse into my baking series (and my kitchen), where I break down all the secrets of pastry and share my tips and techniques.  It’s all crazy delicious and easy, so I hope you’ll tune in and bake along with me! 

♥️ Thank you @joannagaines @chipgaines @chefaz @in2itivecontent @producerweiland @p.mcmahill @madeleinenaomi and the rest of the many, many talented folks (there are dozens) who helped me make this dream come true. I also want to thank my family and friends who dove into this journey with me and made the show feel like home! It takes a village and you’re a spectacular one! #discoveryplus #magnolianetwork #zoebakes #minneapolis #baking #bakers #bake #tvshow #pastry #pastrychef

#ShareTheMicMN Trap or Grow, a five-track rap album and new music video by @appetiteforchange (AFC) Urban Youth, builds on the success of Grow Food. AFC youth wanted to continue sharing music that promotes and popularizes healthy eating and expand the message to encompass the opportunities for young people in North Minneapolis. 
 
You can either ‘trap,’ falling into the streets and the lifestyle that comes with it, or you can ‘grow,’ which means to grow your own food and build your own business. The young people wanted to create a movement encouraging one another to notice and question issues they experience and start creating their own solutions.
 
As youth activism is on the rise, teens feel more empowered than ever, we’ve tried to embrace that drive and encourage them to care about the food they put in their bodies, their community and their future. #kids #rapmusic #creating #urbangarden #growfood #mpls @standard_edition_women

Birthday Carrot Cake with Fresh Flowers (from my garden) for my stepmother, Patricia! I have beautiful purple and blue Hydrangea that bloom every five years, if I’m lucky. I’m not much of a gardener, but my dad and stepmother are near masters at it. So, I thought who better to have these pretty hydrangeas on a cake than Patricia (aka Nana). I’ve had several people ask how I go about decorating with fresh flowers, so I made a Reel to show the process. If the flowers are not edible you have to cover the stems with a special kind of florist tape before you jam them into the icing, see reel. It’s super easy and fast to use. I’ll link to the tape in my stories. Scroll to see the cake from all angles. 🍰🌹🌺🌸🌼

The cake is the carrot cake with Cream Cheese Frosting from Zoë Bakes Cakes. LINK TO RECIPE IN MY @zoebakes BIO.

node.text:
Lemon Honey-Meringue pie! 
It’s all about balance. You need the right ratio of meringue to lemon filling (if you know me, you’ll not be surprised by the skyscraper height of my meringue, compared to the filling) and it needs contrast of textures and flavors. The crust is flaky, but also tender (see 101 PIE CRUST video). The filling is smooth as silk and tart. The finishing touch is a giant pile of meringue made with honey instead of sugar and the best part happens with a blow torch. I know, I’m so predictable, but I love my meringue and 🔥🔥 (see 101 MERINGUE video)! ♥️😂 That burnt meringue is what gives it depth of flavor. And it’s just pure FUN! 

🥧 RECIPE LINK IN @zoebakes BIO! VIDEOS IN MY HIGHLIGHT ARCHIVES! 🔥
 
For more about Pie Dough and how to create a lattice top, you can watch the first episode of Zoë Bakes on the @magnolianetwork through the new app or on @discoveryplus.

Croquembouche on Bastille Day! I went through my archive and found the French-est dessert I could think of to mark this holiday. The Croquembouche is served at weddings and other occasions that deserve a dessert that pulls out all the stops and makes a BIG impression. There is nothing more festive than a tower of cream puffs (profiteroles), this one filled with mango pastry cream (you pick your flavor), dipped in caramel and assembled into a festive centerpiece. But, I’m not done, I added some snowflake cookies (made with @sarah_kieffer’s olive oil sugar cookie dough) and spun up some sugar as a garland. 

It’s a project, but super fun and you can watch the whole thing come together in my HIGHLIGHT video and recipe is on my website (LINK IN @zoebakes BIO). #croquembouche #zoebakes #bakingvideo #bastilleday #cakesofinstagram #cakeoftheday #imsomartha #christmas #christmasdecor #recipeoftheday #holidaydecor #holidayrecipes #caramel #f52grams #marthabakes #sparksjoydaily #beauty #creampuff #centerpiece #frenchfood #pastry #pastrychef #weddingcake #france

Princess Ann’s Yellow Velvet Drip Cake to celebrate her Sweet 16!!! 🎉 A year ago I met Princess Haley and we collaborated on a series of posts about her organizations @appetiteforchange and @breakingbreadmn, but because of Covid we never got to meet. Last week we FINALLY met in person! ♥️ She and her daughter, Princess Ann, gave me a tour of the incredible urban farms, education facilities and cafe where Princess and a bunch of other dedicated people serve the community of North Minneapolis. The gardens are spectacular (scroll to see just one of the farms and the people who make it all grow). The food they prepare with the vegetables is healthy, beautiful, and there is dancing in the kitchen, which you know makes everything taste even better! During Covid they served over 300k meals to people in need of them. Great people doing great work! ♥️🙌🏾 PLEASE GO TO @appetiteforchange for more information and how to donate to their work! I will link in my stories! @breakingbreadmn opens for business tomorrow! 

🎂Back to Princess Ann’s cake, which she designed from the flavors to the dripped white chocolate ganache and fresh roses. The inside layers are “yellow-velvet”, which she came up with and I made from my yellow cake recipe from Zoë Bakes Cakes and a wee bit of natural yellow food dye (turmeric and annatto) to enhance the color. The filling is half passion fruit and half lemon buttercream, because why not have two? She wanted a naked cake, because frosting isn’t her cup of tea, so I did the thinnest layer of white chocolate buttercream on the outside and finished it off with white chocolate drips. This was my very first drip cake and I have to admit it was super fun to do. You can watch me do it in my stories. 💧💧💧

Thank you for inspiring me to try something brand new Princess Ann! Happiest Birthday, it was a true pleasure to be a part of your special day!!! 😘😘 @bby.princess01 you are a remarkable young woman! 

ALL RECIPES CAN BE FOUND IN Zoë Bakes Cakes, LINK IN MY @zoebakes BIO! 🍰

node.text:
Perfect Blueberry Muffins.
Getting back to basics. These may not be the sexiest looking muffin (although I am a sucker for rustic pastry), but they disappear too fast to care what they look like! 🤣 They have a crunchy top and super tender interior with as much fruit as the muffin batter can possibly hold. They’re sweet enough to feel decadent, but not cloyingly so and the flavor is balanced by the blueberries and lemon zest. There are simple tricks to a PERFECT MUFFIN so they don’t become tough or rubbery. .

⭐️ Link to copper baking molds in my Story! 🔥
.
Watch me make the muffins in my IGTV and RECIPE LINK IN MY @zoebakes BIO! You will also find a link to the paper liners and COPPER Molds in the recipe! (I WILL TEACH YOU HOW TO MAKE THE PAPER LINERS IN MY IGTV! The muffins can be made is regular muffin tins as well.) .

node.text:
Kitchen Sink Angel Pie. This pie was the result of testing ALL the fillings for my cake book and having no actual cake to fill. Instead of throwing it all in the freezer for later, I piled the fluffy Swiss meringue (p217) into a pie dish and baked it into a crust. You have to scroll to see the pretty side view  of this pie. The meringue crust is the genius idea I got from my friends at @pieandmightymsp (if you are lucky enough to reside in Mpls, you can order yourself an Angel pie from them - be quick, they’re insanely popular ♥️). Once the meringue was puffed, barely golden and crisp I layered in a whipped milk chocolate mascarpone (p237), some dark chocolate ganache (p221), sticky coconut filling (p233) from my German chocolate cake and topped it with thick caramel sauce (p218). There is no recipe for this one, because they all live in my book, Zoë Bakes Cakes, but it is just proof that experiments can be delicious and I highly recommend you play with your food. ♥️ This would also be great with pastry cream (p231) and fresh fruit or Lemon Curd (p235) and Berries. The combinations are limitless. When you create something, please share and tag me #zoebakescakes #zoebakes @zoebakes, so I don’t miss your bakes!

Caramel Icebox Cake! It’s just too hot, so I’m leaving this here for a little sweet relief. Skip baking your own cookies and this is a no-bake “cake” that’s made in the icebox (fyi - that’s a refrigerator for those of you born after rotary phones went extinct😂). If you’ve never made an icebox cake you’re in for a real treat and it’s crazy easy to put together. I made caramel whipped cream to sandwich between the chocolate wafers and piped it into ruffles. It is both decadent and delicious, but you can experiment with the flavors of both the cream and cookies. Share what you come up with by tagging me #zoebakes @zoebakes so I can see what you create. 

You’ll find the RECIPE LINK IN MY @zoebakes BIO and VIDEO IN my HIGHLIGHTS! 

Stay cool my friends! ❄️❄️

4th of July Desserts! I’ve just spent a couple of days searching for anything frozen and creamy in NYC to beat the crazy heat. It’s got me thinking about baked Alaska, but when am I not thinking about it? 😂 Here are several red, white and blue desserts to make for your holiday celebration, no matter the weather! These RECIPES, plus more on my website, LINK IN MY @zoebakes BIO! 

I also made a red, white and blue pavlova Roulade from Zoë Bakes Cakes for my uncle’s birthday, that would be perfect on the 4th. I have to credit @tschulkin from the @juliachildfoundation for challenging me to create my ultimate summer dessert for the holiday. During the podcast I promised I would, so I am posting the photographic proof that I did indeed make it! 😂♥️🍰🍓🫐And it’s delicious! Scroll to see the pavlova 📷 @kate_childs and modeled by my friend @suencooper!

In Julia’s kitchen Podcast. I had the most delightful conversation with Todd Schulkin from the @juliachildfoundation. We talked about cake, my early obsession with meringue (thanks to Julia) and of course my favorite kitchen tool ~ the Blowtorch! 🔥As is the case with all chefs my views of cooking and teaching were shaped by Julia Child, so it was a true honor to be invited into a conversation about how she formed so much of my baking adventure and introduced me to so many of the bakers I admire most. ♥️

You’ll find our conversation on @heritage_radio wherever you listen to podcasts.
